    "ductTerminal": "Duct terminal — supply register, ceiling diffuser, or return grille. Duct runs end at its collar.",
    "elevator": "A multi-level elevator shaft with configurable openings per level.",
    "eyebrowVent": "Low curved lens-shaped roof vent with a louvered front.",
    "fence": "A straight or curved fence segment with configurable posts and infill.",
    "guide": "A measurement or reference annotation for a line, area, or arc.",
    "gutter": "Rain-water channel running along the eave of a roof segment.",
    "hvacEquipment": "Furnace, air handler, or condenser — duct runs connect to its supply and return collars.",
    "item": "A catalog-backed item such as furniture, a fixture, or decoration.",
